		<div id="comment_body_64184311"><p><div class="quote"><p>&gt;"I remember when Cable TV and Video rentals and Movie Theaters were "Ad Free"</p><p>I am pretty old at this point and don't remember such a time.  CATV ad-free channels didn't last long at all, except for the premium ones.  I think they disappeared before cable came to our neighborhood.  As for theaters, even in my childhood, movies had long previews and concession stand ads.  Yes, it did get worse and worse.  But they were always there.</p><p>I don't mind ads, PSA's, previews, whatever, as long as they are skippable/zoom-past-able.  Before TiVo, I prerecorded everything on VCR for just that reason.  Before that, well, it was horrible.  I would hit mute and do something else... ANYTHING else.  Bathroom, clean, read.  Then resume.  I hated it then, and I will be damned if I ever go back to that hell.</p></div><p>Video rentals were from the 90's and early 2000's before the age of torrents. I'm not sure if they ever introduced ads, but it was less than 20 years ago (at least in Australia).</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64184311">

